Cloudy Bay fashion
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:[Editor's footnote: "A reference to the rough and ready methods used at Cloudy Bay, at the northeast corner of the South Island of New Zealand, where whaleships of many nationalities anchored and whaled in competition with shore stations."]
